title: Maduro says Venezuela will send astronauts to moon on Chinese spaceship
description: After years of drifting away from Beijing, Maduro is strengthening ties with China as he seeks to revive Venezuela’s crumbling economy and oil industry.

title: In Latin America, Brazilian killer who eluded U.S. became cult hero
description: Danilo Cavalcante’s 13-day run transfixed a region that admires U.S. strength while resenting its history of exploitation and interference.

title: CEO calls for more unemployment to give companies upper hand over workers
description: Tim Gurner, who once blamed avocado toast for home-buying challenges, said workers became more “arrogant” after the covid pandemic reshaped the labor market.

title: Libya floods destroy quarter of Derna city; death toll rises to 5,300
description: Amid the soaring death toll there have been some positive signs that Libya’s warring rival governments have put aside their differences to deal with the crisis.

title: Biden administration will track civilian deaths from U.S.-supplied arms
description: U.S. embassy officials will investigate reports of foreign governments suspected of using American-made arms against non-combatants.

title: Ukraine live briefing: Kim-Putin summit starts with ‘all topics’ on the table; missiles hit Crimea shipyard
description: North Korean leader Kim Jong Un is meeting with Russian President Vladimir Putin at a Russian space center. Ukraine launched an assault in Russian-occupied Crimea.

title: Russia ramps up drone, guided bomb attacks to thwart counteroffensive
description: Along with fortified ground defenses like minefields, Russia is using its superior air power, including guided bombs and Lancet drones, to slow Ukraine’s counteroffensive.

title: The gloomy failure of the Oslo accords
description: Three decades later, invoking “Oslo” in the context of the Middle East conjures up a feeling of defeat.

title: North Korea-Russia relations moving to ‘fresh higher level,’ Kim says
description: Russian President Vladimir Putin and North Korea’s Kim Jong Un are expected to meet Wednesday, possibly at a spaceport that is symbol of Moscow’s ambitions for space flight.

title: Members of Congress are planning official visits to China
description: Two congressional delegations, including one led by Senate Majority Leader Charles E. Schumer, are planning to visit China amid simmering tensions with Beijing.
